This Version adds new Gem Settings!

randomizeGems: If gems are randomized, 1: yes; 0: no

gemsRequired: What percentage of gems (Rounded down) is required to open the final final door

0.11.0.description:
Upon starting a save all Endings unlocked in Archipelago are unlocked in the save as well. This allows continuing where you left if you loose your save or take over from someone else.
The ending above the castle now also triggers Ending 17
The signs at the ultimate door now reveal your settings. The left one tells you how many endings you need and the right one tells you how many gems you need.
0.11.0.title: Version 0.11.0

0.12.0.description:
Implemented the progressive swords.

Sword 1 spawns the sword in the treasureroom on the mountain
Sword 2 spawns the sword next to the elder
Sword 3 spawns the sword at home

Picking up any of the swords disables the otherones for this run

Sword 1 can be disabled in logic using the setting "treasureSword". If set to false, the treasure sword will not be in the item pool and won't be considered for the logic

0.15.2.description:
THIS RELEASE IS PRE ALPHA. DO NOT USE IT OUTSIDE OF MULTIWORLDS SPECIFICALLY GENERATED TO TEST THIS. IT IS NOT BACKWARDS COMPATIBLE WITH ANY PREVIOUS VERSION!

Please read everything below this to make sure you know what you sign up for.

Disclaimer: This release exists to share this very early version of a new method to generate the logic. To be able to use interesting new features like e.g. random spawn locations and random item locations it goes through an incredibly convoluted process. Due to this generating even a single Reventure seed takes a lot of time. During my tests it could take up to 10 minutes! This will be improved in the future (Hopefully otherwise this is pretty useless...).
This version might break during gen. It might break at the end of generation after 10 minutes. It might also contain broken logic and thus lead to worlds that are unbeatable. Please report any and all bugs you find in the discord! If at all possible include the multiworld if you got that far.

Some of the endings are disabled in this version:
Both desert endings
Greedy Bastard
Sustainable Development

Some of the settings do nothing in this version:
hardJumps is always enabled
hardcombat is always enabled
treasuresword doesn't exist

Also I suggest setting endings not to high (e.g. below 40) and accesibility to minimal this should reduce generation failures.

Player Facing there is one new feature: Random Spawn Locations. The start location is one of ca. 60 Locations. It could even be Lonks House!
0.15.2.title: Version 0.15.2

0.19.0.description:
## Better Nonstopmodes!

DISCLAIMER: This Version is NOT compatible with previous APWorlds!

The game now supports different Nonstopmodes. Every "higher" option also includes all "lower" options:
- Off: Turns off nonstopmode. All endings will restart your run. Just like in the vanilla game.
- Canonical: This includes endings where I decided that it "makes sense" that you don't die. For example: Destroying all pots or stabbing people! This is purely based on the ingame action and not on the ending cutscene.
- Logical: This includes all endings where turning them on does not break logic. For example: Jumping of cliffs or getting killed by the dragon. This does not include endings where you don't die but are softlocked (e.g. the infinite hole)
- Everything: This includes... everything*. Some of these allow you to break logic, because you are invincible, can walk through spikes and lava or because hugging the boulder lets you skip past it.

A few endings are not implemented because they are weird. I do want to implement them at some point though:
- PickupAnvil
- All Cannon Endings
- Getting killed by minions
- And of course my all time favourite: The whistle ending.

For a quick guide on which option to pick:
- Pick "off" if you do not want to play with this feature. Particularly if you have not played the vanilla game!
- Pick "canonical" if you care about the "story"
- Pick "logical" if you want the most endings possible to be skipped without affecting logic (This is the "suggested" setting)
- Pick "everything" if you are crazy

Some of these lists are subjective. Feel free to make an argument for endings that should switch their category!

Also I do want to add the option for a custom list in the future! That way you can just add any ending you want.
